title: Esophageal cancer cases in England 2017 , by age and gender
summary: This grouped bar chart represents New registrations on the Y-axis. And, how the value changed throughout 15 Months for Men, and Women.
All through the Months, similar trend was observed for Women and Men. In both cases, the New registrations have grew.
In Month 70-74, Men had the highest New registrations 1037.0 among the 2 groups and in 20-24, Women had the lowest New registrations 1.0.
In Month 70-74, Women had the highest New registrations among all 15 Months and it has the lowest New registrations in Month 20-24.

max_summary: This grouped bar chart represents New registrations on the Y-axis. And, how the value changed throughout 15 Months for Men, and Women.
Over the 15 Months, the New registrations for both Women and Men have grew.
In Month 70-74, Men had the highest New registrations 1037.0 among the 2 groups and in 20-24, Women had the lowest New registrations 1.0.
Among all the Months, Women had the highest New registrations 372.0 in Month 70-74 and lowest value 1.0 in Month 20-24.
There is a gap of 371.0 between the highest and lowest New registrations found for Women in Month 70-74 and 20-24.
Among all 2 groups, Men had the gap of 1033.0 between the maximum and minimum New registrations observed in Month 70-74 and 20-24 respectively.
Averaging all 2 groups Men, and Women, the Month 70-74 is the maximum New registrations and 20-24 is the minimum New registrations.
